OL,3,C'Exceptional wet weather' sinks farmer
OL,4,Cconfidence to all-time low
OL,6,FRelentless wet conditions in autumn
OL,7,Fplayed a big part, according to the
OL,8,FNFU, with 82% of survey respondents
OL,9,Fsaying their farm businesses suffered
OL,10,Fnegative impacts.
OL,12,FBut since January, heavy rain and
OL,13,Fstorms continued to batter the UK
OL,14,Fthrough to April, meaning results
OL,15,Fwould likely be worse if the survey
OL,16,Fwere taken today.
OL,18,FTom Bradshaw, NFU president, said the
OL,19,Fextreme weather was part of "the
OL,20,Fperfect storm of events coming
OL,21,Ftogether".
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/15
